title: Russian air force says hit '10 Islamic State targets' in Syria - Region - World
text:
Related Official: US questions Russian flight incursion into Turkey Iraqi Shia militia welcomes Russian action against Islamic State, criticises US Russia violation of Turkey airspace likely not accidental: US official Russia cannot fight Islamic State and support Assad in Syria: Britain says Russian military jets carried out 15 new sorties Monday, targeting 10 Islamic State targets, the defence ministry said.
"Su-34, Su-24M and Su-25 carried out 15 sorties from the Hmeimim airbase in the afternoon," the ministry said in a statement, adding that 10 facilities had been struck.
